cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on analyzing the impact of relays on the uplink performance of cellular networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of decoding techniques such as Successive Interference Cancellation and Superposition Coding, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with the performance of wireless cellular networks, which is a topic covered under communications and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the impact of relays on the performance of cellular networks, which can be seen as a control problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the impact of relays on the throughput and energy saving of cellular networks, which can be related to multimedia applications.
